data.title: The Miller Group
data.meta_description: Get To Know Us Our people are our biggest asset. We’ve built years of experience in insurance, benefits and risk to help you protect what you have built.
data.text:
I am an outdoor enthusiast. My favorite times are spent in the forest and mountains camping, hiking, fishing, and exploring with friends and family. My beautiful wife and I have three adventurous boys.

I have a mini aussiedoodle named Frank. I like to read, and I enjoy spending time hiking on the weekends.

I’m an optimist who loves to laugh and escape to the lake. You’ll often find me singing in the car. I enjoy connecting with new people, chatting over a coffee.

From mastering the ski slopes at age 50 to soaking up the sun in Cabo, I’m all about joy and adventure. My husband and I have a daughter, plus two chocolate labs, making life delightfully busy.

I love being with my husband and three sons! We like to explore national parks together. Don’t ask me about gardening unless you are ready for a long discussion!

I’m a serial hobbyist who enjoys spending time with my wife, dog, family, and friends when I’m not water skiing, woodworking, golfing, hunting, barbequing, gardening, or watching sports. I’m a fan of KU basketball and all KC sports teams.

I’m a Royals baseball, Chiefs football, and KU basketball fan. I stay active by running, biking, and playing beach volleyball with friends. I enjoy spending time with my wife and daughter.

I have a golden retriever who I love more than anything. I’ve been to over 150 concerts and still counting. I went skydiving on my first date with my boyfriend.

I’m a travel enthusiast who will rarely turn down a trip, so I’m slowly but surely checking destinations off my bucket list. I love sports, but I’m much better at watching and cheering than playing. I have 5 nieces and nephews who mean the world to me and I can’t say no to them.

I’m a travel enthusiast who will rarely turn down a trip, so I’m slowly but surely checking destinations off my bucket list. I love sports, but I’m much better at watching and cheering than playing. I have 5 nieces and nephews who mean the world to me and I can’t say no to them.

My brisket once finished in the top 25 in the Kansas State Championship. I invented and built a new-(but not so)-improved type of lawnmower in college. Some of my best travel adventures are by accident.

I’m a family man with a crazy quintet of kids. I enjoy the outdoors. I love spending time with others while playing cards and board games.

I’m a mom to an enthusiastic and entertaining son. I’m a bit ambidextrous; I only write with my left hand and do many other things right-handed. I love Mexican food and will never turn down chips and salsa.

I am passionate about giving back to the community through various board involvements and committees. I love all things KC sports and Creighton Basketball. I love golfing.

I am an enthusiast for music and art! In my free time you can find me traveling to National Parks to go hiking, doing a yoga class and cooking and baking.

I enjoy spending time with my family. I served on the board for United Cerebral Palsy and remain active and involved in the community. I enjoy golf, tennis, and all of our local sports teams.

I love golfing and trying the latest food spots in KC. My favorite place to visit is Colorado where I hike and ski.

I am a licensed pilot. I travel to Mexico with my Spanish-speaking wife every year. I am the unofficial winner of “best Halloween costume” every year.

I restore homes and 1950s vehicles. I reside on a horse farm in Peculiar, MO. I winter part-time with my wife in Scottsdale, AZ.

My wife and I have a full house of four children, two boys and two girls! If I am not watching my boys on the soccer field, daughter on the volleyball court, or chasing our youngest around, you can find me on a golf course, watching Sporting Kansas City, or cheering on the Chiefs!

My wife and I have a full house of four children, two boys and two girls! If I am not watching my boys on the soccer field, daughter on the volleyball court, or chasing our youngest around, you can find me on a golf course, watching Sporting Kansas City, or cheering on the Chiefs!

I’ve completed 8 marathons, a half-Ironman and several adventure races. I have a degree in Education but was never a teacher. I enjoy playing golf, going on motorcycle camping trips, and boating with friends.

I'm the mom of a crazy little boy with a huge personality. I bleed Chiefs red and Royals blue. I can beat you at any Super Mario game.

I am a mom of three wonderful children. I enjoy playing tennis in my spare time. I'm happiest when I'm at the lake.

I am a mother to two lovely daughters and one generously sweet son. Sunny, warm places make me happy. Drinking iced coffee everyday is a must!

I enjoy traveling in our RV with my family and our Whippet. We’re also foodies that love cooking and trying out new recipes.

I am the best Cool Aunt to my niece and nephews. I am a classically trained chef. I am a certified bookworm.

I thrive on creativity in all forms: numbers, music, art, and song. I love solving problems with new solutions. I love being in the mountains and on the water… skiing on anything that moves.

I am a grammar geek. I am a dog lover. I can interpret legalese for you.

I’m a scratch bowler and bowled collegiately for UCM. I love sports, especially Chiefs football. I have an almost photographic memory and can recall lots of trivia, especially about movies.

I can say the ABCs backwards really fast, I took some classes in Mandarin, I am left-handed.

I am a mother of two kids. I have one daughter and one son who are 10 years apart. I enjoy hanging out with my friends and family, playing with my kids, and watching movies. The ocean is my happy place but any body of water will do.

I am a mother of two kids. I have one daughter and one son who are 10 years apart. I enjoy hanging out with my friends and family, playing with my kids, and watching movies. The ocean is my happy place but any body of water will do.

I have three grandchildren I love being goofy with. Animals and nature are important to me, and I subscribe to 4Ocean to support ocean and beach cleanup.

With 3 daughters and 4 granddaughters, my life is not devoid of drama. Baseball is part of my DNA and I played in 2 college world series for MU. I’m passionate about health and wellbeing.

My wife Hannah and I have 2 boys, Hank and Cooper. If we aren’t chasing the boys around you can find us on the golf course as a family having a blast! We enjoy being outside exploring the country, especially the mountains.

My wife Hannah and I have 2 boys, Hank and Cooper. If we aren’t chasing the boys around you can find us on the golf course as a family having a blast! We enjoy being outside exploring the country, especially the mountains.

I love to learn and create. As a mom to three boys, we spend lots of time outdoors exploring, so we have more rocks than you can imagine. I’ve visited 48 of the 50 states and hope to make it to the last two soon!

I love to learn and create. As a mom to three boys, we spend lots of time outdoors exploring, so we have more rocks than you can imagine. I’ve visited 48 of the 50 states and hope to make it to the last two soon!

I am the 5th of 6 children and enjoy being the fun uncle, watching my nieces and nephews grow over the years and hope to have a family of my own one day. I also enjoy golfing and playing basketball with friends.

I am the 5th of 6 children and enjoy being the fun uncle, watching my nieces and nephews grow over the years and hope to have a family of my own one day. I also enjoy golfing and playing basketball with friends.

I am a mother of two. I love to garden – until I see a snake. I love to fish – until I see a snake.

I am the father of 6 kids, grandfather of 13 and growing. I have walked on hot coals, waterskied barefoot, and played on first-team college tennis. I am now much more interested in spending time with my family at home and my work family!

I am the father of 6 kids, grandfather of 13 and growing. I have walked on hot coals, waterskied barefoot, and played on first-team college tennis. I am now much more interested in spending time with my family at home and my work family!

I’m marrying my high school sweetheart. The lake is my favorite place to escape to but the mountains are a close second. I love all things true crime.

I am a mother to a wonderful little girl. I love spending time outside with my family and friends. I enjoy reading a good book and cooking.

You will find me chasing my 2 girls around, frequenting area parks and spending time with our extended family any chance we get. I’m known for never meeting a stranger and my blunt humor!

I believe communication is key, there is no such thing as a stranger, and having a sense of humor is a must.

I am my daughters’ biggest fan on and off the softball field. I golf to wind down and relax. I advocate for nonprofits & my motto is “no margin, no mission.”

I enjoy serving my church, playing with my grandchildren, and reading. I have been married for over thirty-five years and have four beautiful granddaughters.

I am an alumnus of Rockhurst High School and Regis University. I am passionate about giving back. I bleed red and yellow… Go Chiefs!

I am a devout Catholic, husband and father of 4 awesome kids and an amazing grandson. I love the Chiefs, the Royals and the lake!

I have an amazing husband and two wonderful sons who keep us very busy. Each weekend you can find us headed to a coffee shop with our dogs in tow for their expected weekly donut holes.

I am an avid reader who loves to travel through fictional settings and the real-world. I enjoy spending time with friends, family and my adorable dog, Bo. I’m a terrible cook, but I still try!

I am the mother of three kids and two dogs. I enjoy spending time with my family and friends outside, playing sports, and being on the lake. Visiting and hiking every U.S. National Park with my husband is on my bucket list.

I am the mother of three kids and two dogs. I enjoy spending time with my family and friends outside, playing sports, and being on the lake. Visiting and hiking every U.S. National Park with my husband is on my bucket list.

Family and community have always been priorities in my life. My home is known as “the fun house” because we’re always having company over.

I am a Yale soccer mom. I enjoy spending time in my garden. I have a bit of a sweet tooth.

I consider my happy place to be anywhere outdoors. I’m grabbing my passport if I hear the word “travel”. I Watched Sound of Music and Grease until the VCR wore out as a kid.

Brad Pitt is my 4th cousin once removed (but I’ve never met him), I once bungee jumped from a 200ft crane. I fell out of a moving car but wasn’t severely injured when I was 3.

I have a passion for reading. I love hanging out with family and friends. I’d use my inside voice…if I had one!

I have yet to meet a beach I don’t love. I can get lost in reading a good book. My heart is in spending time with my husband, kids, 3 grandsons and 1 granddaughter.

I am the mother of a busy high school boy and enjoy spending time with him, my husband, and our rescue pup. I’m a huge bookworm. I love to travel!

I’m the proud father to an amazing daughter and played baseball at collegiate and professional levels. I have two dogs, including a 20-year old rescue a fraternity brother pawned off on me in college.

I enjoy Greek mythology, reading historical fiction and laughing with my family of jokesters. I seem to hiccup at least three times a days.

I enjoy spending time with family and friends. My wife and I have two amazing children who keeps us very busy. I’m an avid sports fan who enjoys playing golf and basketball in my free time.
